Package: fastmlm
Title: Fast Estimation of Multilevel Linear Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ross A.", "Dunne", email = "sadneurons@pm.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits linear mixed-effects models 4-14x faster than 'lme4' using a
    high-performance C++ backend. Features include a custom formula parser,
    formula/data caching for repeated fits (bootstrap, simulation), a C++
    L-BFGS-B optimiser with gradient computation, CHOLMOD supernodal sparse
    Cholesky factorisation (via the 'Matrix' package), precomputed sparse matrix
    mappings for zero-allocation deviance updates, optional GPU acceleration via
    CUDA, Satterthwaite degrees of freedom, and integration with 'emmeans' and
    'broom.mixed'. Provides a drop-in interface using the same formula syntax as
    lmer() from 'lme4'.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
